data.database_description: The database schema described is designed to manage and organize medical records and operations within a healthcare facility. It includes tables for tracking physicians, departments, patients, nurses, appointments, procedures, medications, hospital rooms, and patient stays. The relationships between these tables are established through foreign keys, ensuring data integrity and allowing for comprehensive querying of the system. The database supports various functionalities such as scheduling appointments, managing patient care, tracking medical treatments, and monitoring staff assignments within different departments and blocks of the hospital.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each physician.
Full name of the physician.
The job position of the physician.
The social security number of the physician.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about physicians working in the hospital.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each department.
Name of the department.
The ID of the physician who is the head of the department.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about different departments in the hospital.

columns.columnDescription: The ID of the physician.
The ID of the department.
Indicates if this is the primary affiliation of the physician with the department.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks the affiliation of physicians with departments.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each procedure.
Name of the procedure.
Cost associated with performing the procedure.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about medical procedures available in the healthcare facility.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier for the physician, linked to the Physician table.
Code of the procedure, linked to the Procedures table.
The date when the physician was certified for the procedure.
The expiration date of the physician's certification for the procedure.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about physicians' certifications for specific procedures.

columns.columnDescription: Unique Social Security Number of the patient.
Full name of the patient.
Mailing address of the patient.
Contact phone number of the patient.
Identifier for the patient's insurance coverage.
Primary Care Physician ID, linking to the physician table.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about patients including personal details and medical insurance.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each nurse.
Full name of the nurse.
Job title or role of the nurse.
Indicates whether the nurse is registered (1) or not (0).
Social Security number of the nurse.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about nurses in the healthcare facility.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each appointment.
SSN of the patient attending the appointment.
Employee ID of the nurse responsible for preparing the patient for the appointment.
Employee ID of the physician conducting the appointment.
Scheduled start time of the appointment.
Scheduled end time of the appointment.
The room number where the appointment will take place.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Records appointments made by patients with physicians.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each medication.
Name of the medication.
Brand name or manufacturer of the medication.
Brief description or additional information about the medication.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about different medications available in the healthcare facility.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier for the physician who prescribed the medication.
Social Security Number (SSN) of the patient receiving the prescription.
Code representing the medication prescribed.
Date and time when the medication was prescribed.
Identifier for the appointment during which the prescription was made.
Amount or dosage of the medication prescribed.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Records each instance where a physician prescribes a medication to a patient.

columns.columnDescription: The floor number of the block.
A unique identifier for the block.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about hospital blocks, including their floor and code.

columns.columnDescription: The unique number assigned to each room.
The type of room (e.g., Single, Double).
The floor number where the room is located.
The block code where the room is located.
Indicates whether the room is currently unavailable (1) or available (0).

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores details about individual rooms within the hospital, including their type, location, and availability.

columns.columnDescription: Reference to the Nurse's EmployeeID indicating which nurse is on call.
The floor number of the block where the nurse is on call.
A code representing a specific area or room within the hospital block.
The start time of the nurse's on-call shift.
The end time of the nurse's on-call shift.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about nurses' on-call shifts in different hospital blocks.

columns.columnDescription: A unique identifier for each stay record.
The SSN of the patient staying in the room.
The room number where the patient is staying.
The start date and time of the patient's stay.
The end date and time of the patient's stay.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Records patient stays in rooms, including the start and end dates of their stay.

columns.columnDescription: Foreign key to the Patient table, representing the patient who underwent the procedure.
Foreign key to the Procedures table, identifying the specific procedure performed.
Foreign key to the Stay table, indicating the hospital stay during which the procedure occurred.
The date and time when the procedure was performed.
Foreign key to the Physician table, identifying the doctor who conducted the procedure.
Foreign key to the Nurse table, identifying the nurse who assisted during the procedure.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Records procedures undergone by patients during their stays.
